  "texts": [
    "The communication between the application and the LLM happens in the background, and users (students or teachers) are not exposed to the technical details of these exchanges.",
    "The system processes each prompt and interaction internally, following a structured format that instructs the LLM on how to generate feedback.We use the API (Application Programming Interface) provided by OpenAI to enable the interaction between the LEAP system and the LLM.",
    "An API is a set of protocols that allows different software applications to communicate with each other.",
    "Through the API, LEAP sends instructions to the LLM, and returns feedback based on the inputs it receives.",
    "The messages sent to the LLM are organized as a list of dictionaries (i.e., specific prompts), with each dictionary representing a message."
  ],
